Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Mince a few slices until you have 3 TBSP. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} and @bell pepper{1}. Dice @Roma tomatoes{2}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest @lime{1} until you have 1 tsp zest; quarter lime. In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomatoes, minced onion, cilantro, juice from 2 lime wedges, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a #small pot{}, combine 1 ½ cups water, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ½ tsp @turmeric{1%tsp}(save the rest for another use), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Turn off heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion, poblano, bell pepper, half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside.

Pat @chicken breast strips{20%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat another large drizzle of oil in pan used to cook veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with @chili powder{1%tsp} and remaining Southwest spice blend. Cook, stirring, until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir in remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¼ cup water, @butter{2%tbsp}, and cooked veggies until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{6%tbsp}, lime zest, 1 tsp water, and juice from remaining lime wedges. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside ⅓ of the rice and ⅓ of the chicken mixture for lunch. Divide remaining rice and chicken between bowls. Top with half the salsa. Drizzle with crema and 1 packet hot sauce.

Divide remaining rice, remaining chicken mixture, and remaining salsa between @flour tortillas{2}. Roll into burritos and place in #reusable containers{}. Pack remaining sour cream and @hot sauce{3%tsp} alongside. Reheat burritos in #microwave{} before enjoying. Serve with sour cream and hot sauce.

> Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight's dinner extras transform into tomorrow's lunch. That's thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). For the first meal in this 2-in-1 recipe, fluffy turmeric rice is piled with spiced chicken, a tangle of onions and peppers, fresh salsa, and a dollop of zesty lime crema. The next day, this bowl-tastic meal is effortlessly bundled up into a burrito for a hearty, eat-it-anywhere lunch.